GIT
git init - creates a new Git repository
git status - inspects the contents of the working directory and staging area
git add - adds files from the working directory to the staging area
git diff - shows the difference between the working directory and the staging area
git commit - permanently stores file changes from the staging area in the repository
git log - shows a list of all previous commits

Commands related to remote repository:
git clone https://github.com/user-name/repository-name.git
git push origin master
Commands related to workflow:
git add .
git commit -m "A message describing what you have done to make this snapshot different"
Commands related to checking status or log history
git status
git log

What is the role of HTML in a web page? - how the web page is STRUCTURED
What is the role of CSS in a web page? -  how it LOOKS 
What is the role of Javascript in a web page? - how it FUNCTIONS
